I'm hopeful that that is going
to happen within

32:05.290 --> 32:07.159 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our lifetime.

32:07.192 --> 32:14.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Kelly Rodriguez
is Michael's
wife. She's a platoon sergeant
with the 18th

32:14.699 --> 32:21.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Airborne Corps at Fort Bragg in
North Carolina.
She too suffers from PTSD. She
practically

32:21.239 --> 32:24.176 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had to beg her doctors to get an
accurate
diagnosis.

32:24.209 --> 32:27.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How many deployments have you
done in your
20-plus years?

32:27.412 --> 32:29.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ,
U.S. Army:
Five.

32:30.015 --> 32:32.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: What was your
most traumatizing
posting?

32:33.018 --> 32:36.021 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
My last deployment.

32:36.054 --> 32:37.322 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: In Afghanistan.

32:37.355 --> 32:39.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
In Afghanistan
2009 to 2010.

32:39.291 --> 32:44.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: Kelly served as
a medic,
treating casualties from one of
the bloodiest

32:44.229 --> 32:50.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
attacks on U.S. troops in
Afghanistan. Kelly
and her team saw hundreds of
trauma patients

32:50.802 --> 32:53.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
go through the operating room
that year.

32:53.271 --> 32:59.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
It's not just
engaging in combat. It's seeing
it. And when

32:59.244 --> 33:05.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
