NCO came
in, and he's holding his arm.

33:12.290 --> 33:18.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: One patient hit
her the hardest,
a female soldier who volunteered
for a convoy

33:18.797 --> 33:22.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so she could see her husband
before he shipped
out.

33:22.167 --> 33:25.437 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
The convoy
was hit and -- by an IED.

33:25.470 --> 33:27.272 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: By an IED?

33:27.305 --> 33:33.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
she was alive
when she got to us, but she
died. And her

33:33.945 --> 33:36.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
husband was there. And I think
the reason
it was really hard is because,
if Michael

33:36.648 --> 33:41.987 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was downrange, I would have done
the same
thing. That could have been me.

33:42.020 --> 33:48.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: After returning
home, Kelly
suspected that she might have
PTSD, but trying

33:48.493 --> 33:53.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to get an accurate diagnosis was
a difficult
ordeal for her too.

33:53.131 --> 33:58.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
It came down
to screaming. Find out if it is
PTS. Great.

33:58.603 --> 34:03.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If it's not, great. One way or
the other,
I need something, besides, you
have got anxiety

34:03.608 --> 34:04.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and you're depressed.

34:04.576 --> 34:07.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, you know, so does half of
America.

34:07.646 --> 34:12.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: It took more
than two years
before Kelly was finally
diagnosed with PTSD.

34:12.784 --> 34:16.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
You can't
treat it if you don't put your
hands on it,

34:16.254 --> 34:23.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
put a name on it. And that's
why, for me,
it was frustrating trying to get
any diagnosis.

34:23.428 --> 34:30.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: A shortfall
they both hope
science will someday resolve.

34:30.135 --> 34:35.473 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Will someone who is just
entering the military
10 years from now have a
completely different

34:35.507 --> 34:37.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
