you both had?

34:37.309 --> 34:40.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SGT. 1ST CLASS MICHAEL
RODRIGUEZ: I hope there
is. That would be fantastic.

34:40.078 --> 34:43.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SGT. 1ST CLASS KELLY RODRIGUEZ:
Because, at
the end of the day, if there is
something

34:43.348 --> 34:46.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
going on with them, they want to
know what
it is.

34:46.117 --> 34:51.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SOLEDAD O'BRIEN: For the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm
Soledad O'Brien in Fayetteville,
North Carolina.

34:51.756 --> 34:56.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Our series War on
the Brain
concludes Friday with a look at
the efforts

34:56.695 --> 35:07.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to find the true cause of PTSD.

