scholars at

35:39.604 --> 35:41.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Indiana University.

35:41.473 --> 35:44.409 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And welcome to the "NewsHour" to
both of you.

35:44.442 --> 35:48.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reported
today -- and I
will start with you, Senator
Lugar -- that

35:48.646 --> 35:54.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the United States is expanding
-- expanding
and deepening its military
involvement in

35:54.753 --> 36:01.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Middle East under President
Trump in Iraq,
in Syria, in Yemen. At the same
time, he's

36:01.826 --> 36:06.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
calling for cutbacks in spending
on diplomacy.

36:06.731 --> 36:08.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you think of this
approach?

36:08.466 --> 36:12.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD LUGAR (R), Former U.S.
Senator: Well,
I believe the approach is very
fearful.

36:12.370 --> 36:19.577 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we really need to have all
of our alliances
as strong as possible. I mean,
as a matter

36:19.611 --> 36:26.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of fact, to have a military
strategy for the
Middle East, as opposed to a few
troops that

36:26.184 --> 36:34.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are going here and there at
various times,
I'm really concerned about the
president's

36:34.592 --> 36:38.963 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
lack of enthusiasm for NATO, for
example.

36:38.997 --> 36:45.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm worried about our -- even
the alliance
problems in our own hemisphere
with the NAFTA,

36:45.837 --> 36:50.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
quite apart from those ties with
the Far East.
In other words, we need to reach
out, offering

36:50.508 --> 36:56.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leadership in the world. And we
need to be
finding new allies, new people
to help us.

36:56.281 --> 37:01.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Middle East will not be
solved by a few
Americans who are sent over
there, even if

37:01.886 --> 37:03.888 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we augment that by a few more.

37:03.922 --> 37:07.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Representative
Hamilton, your
take on the first two months of
this presidency

37:07.425 --> 37:09.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on foreign policy?

37:09.227 --> 37:13.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE HAMILTON (D), Former U.S.
Congressman:
Well, I agree very much with
what Dick said.

37:13.731 --> 37:22.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You need to have I a strong
military and be
prepared to use it on occasion
as a last resort.

37:22.140 --> 37:26.411 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But you certainly have to have
strong diplomacy.

37:26.444 --> 37:31.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Almost all of these problems
that we're dealing
with, I think all of them,
ultimately have

37:31.716 --> 37:38.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a political solution. You do not
get that
kind of a solution through
military action.

37:38.690 --> 37:46.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You get it through diplomacy,
negotiations,
consultations, endless meetings,
and conversations

37:46.498 --> 37:50.635 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of all kinds with your friends
and your enemies.

37:50.668 --> 37:56.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We need a strong diplomatic
effort in order
to advance our interests in the
world.

37:56.908 --> 38:00.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, between the
two of you,
you served, I think, a total of
more than

38:00.879 --> 38:05.583 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- of 70 years, between the U.S.
Senate and
the U.S. House.

38:05.617 --> 38:09.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senator Lugar, what is it
exactly that you
would like to see the president
do when it

38:09.320 --> 38:11.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
comes to diplomacy that he isn't
doing right
now?

38:11.856 --> 38:16.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD LUGAR: Well, first of
all, he needs
to indicate that we are not
going to cut the

38:16.928 --> 38:22.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
budget of the State Department,
that we're
not going to cut foreign aid or
potential

38:22.400 --> 38:25.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
assistance even to starving
people around
the world.

38:25.270 --> 38:32.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In other words, we really need a
burst of
enthusiasm for American
humanitarianism, American

38:32.810 --> 38:38.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reach-out to other countries and
other people.
We have those resources here.
They're tremendously

38:38.783 --> 38:40.518 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
important.

38:40.552 --> 38:45.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we are the leader. It won't
do really
just to augment the defense
budgets, while

38:45.490 --> 38:50.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you're cutting back foreign aid
and you're
cutting back on treaties. We
have already

38:51.029 --> 38:56.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seen the dissolution of the
Pacific pact.
That's a treaty for foreign
trade.

38:56.534 --> 39:03.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are already seeing the
diminishing interest
of foreign trade generally by
the president,

39:03.241 --> 39:08.813 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a diminishing of Americans
accepting other
people coming into our country.

39:08.846 --> 39:13.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We really need to sort of
reverse these courses
and get back into American
leadership.

39:13.718 --> 39:16.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we should
note that is
coming from a Republican.

39:17.021 --> 39:22.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Representative Hamilton, what is
the formula
that you see? What would you
like to see this

39:22.260 --> 39:26.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president do, say that we
haven't heard or
seen so far?

39:26.831 --> 39:33.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE HAMILTON: Look, I think
American leadership
in the world is absolutely
necessary.

39:33.471 --> 39:39.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I come from the school of
thought -- and I
think Dick does too -- that
American leadership,

39:39.110 --> 39:47.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
though not perfect, we make
mistakes, is crucial
to progress in the world,
economic growth,

39:47.118 --> 39:52.824 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
peace and stability, extension
of freedom
and liberty to all people.

39:52.857 --> 39:57.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have to step forward and
take on that
burden of leadership. And that's
what the

39:57.762 --> 40:05.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president has to do. If you look
back over
the past hundred days or so of
the Trump administration,

40:05.136 --> 40:11.542 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
all of the news has been
internal or external
problems of the Trump
administration.

40:11.576 --> 40:18.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's having a very hard time
getting started
and exerting his authority as a
president

40:18.549 --> 40:23.254 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because of these internal and
some external
problems.

40:23.288 --> 40:29.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The world needs our leadership
in all kinds
of ways. And we have to step up
to that responsibility.

40:29.861 --> 40:36.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, if we do not do it, then
others will
fill the vacuum. We have a
marvelous record

40:37.001 --> 40:43.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of global leadership over
decades since World
War II. We have got a -- we see
signs now

40:43.741 --> 40:48.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that that leadership may be
waning in some
respects.

40:48.279 --> 40:54.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we have to step up our game,
assert our
leadership. And President Trump
has to take

40:54.652 --> 41:02.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the lead on that, so that the
United States
can fulfill the expectations of
the world

41:02.694 --> 41:06.130 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for our leadership for good
around the world.

41:06.164 --> 41:11.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Two distinguished
American
lawmakers, Representative Lee
Hamilton, Senator

41:11.636 --> 41:12.837 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Richard Lugar.

41:12.870 --> 41:15.807 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's very good to see both of
you again. We
thank you.

41:15.840 --> 41:20.144 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RICHARD LUGAR: Thanks so much.

41:20.178 --> 41:23.648 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LEE HAMILTON: Thank you.

41:23.681 --> 41:29.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: teaching the
youngest
of kids about the basics of
money.

41:29.921 --> 41:34.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our economics correspondent Paul
Solman looks
at how parents can help their
children learn

41:34.592 --> 41:36.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
