41:40.398 --> 41:44.135 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHILD: Maybe there's some candy
in there.

41:44.168 --> 41:47.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: In Arlington,
Virginia, an unusual
venue for little kids.

41:47.372 --> 41:48.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER, Personal Finance
Expert: Who
knows where we are now?

41:48.773 --> 41:51.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILD: America, Virginia,
Washington, D.C.,
at the bank.

41:51.642 --> 41:54.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: What does a bank
do?

41:54.178 --> 41:57.115 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHILD: A bank gives you money
and stuff.

41:57.148 --> 42:00.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: They just hand it
out?

42:00.451 --> 42:01.419 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILD: I think so.

42:01.452 --> 42:03.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Where does the bank
get money?

42:03.454 --> 42:06.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHILD: I think it gets it from a
sock.

42:06.457 --> 42:07.759 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: From a sock?

42:07.792 --> 42:09.527 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: A sock?

42:09.560 --> 42:13.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Personal finance guru Beth
Kobliner thinks
kids should be learning about
money early.

42:13.731 --> 42:15.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
But they're not.

42:15.566 --> 42:20.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: I think parents
are much more
likely to talk about sex or
drugs or alcohol

42:20.738 --> 42:22.907 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with their children than they
are about money.

42:22.940 --> 42:29.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Kobliner hopes to
break the taboo
with a new book, "Make Your Kid
a Money Genius,"

42:29.046 --> 42:33.618 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that continues work she's been
doing for years.

42:33.651 --> 42:38.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kobliner has been teaching key
concepts in
economics. She insists kids can
learn them

42:38.890 --> 42:40.658 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
young.

42:40.691 --> 42:48.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BETH KOBLINER: By age 3,
children can understand
basic money concepts like
exchange, or we

42:49.000 --> 42:52.336 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have to make choices, or things
have a value.

42:52.370 --> 42:58.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And those conversations are
important to start
when kids are really little. By
age 7, a lot

42:58.142 --> 43:03.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of those behaviors to do with
money, whether
it's self-control or delayed
gratification,

43:03.748 --> 43:09.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they start getting set. So,
those ages 3 to
7, it's really kind of a nice
sweet spot in

43:09.854 --> 43:12.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which parents should be talking
to their kids
about money.

43:12.457 --> 43:16.494 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: We gathered our own
group of
kids to try it out.

43:16.527 --> 43:19.330 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
