to the bank?

43:19.363 --> 43:24.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHILD: My mommy and daddy work
and get money.
And they buy milk for me.

43:24.735 --> 43:26.637 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: There you go?

43:26.671 --> 43:30.908 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And you're how old? You're? Just
3 years old.

43:30.942 --> 43:36.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Another key concept all kids
should know,
says Kobliner: what it means to
work for a

43:36.414 --> 43:38.316 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
living, like here at the
"NewsHour."

43:38.349 --> 43:42.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: You bring your
kid to your
office, and they see where you
work. This

43:42.086 --> 43:46.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
woman I know, she said her dad
would leave
every morning when she was
little with a newspaper

43:46.591 --> 43:51.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
under his arm. And she thought,
oh, my dad's
job is reading the newspaper
every day.

43:51.729 --> 43:55.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then years later, she found
out, oh, he's
a teacher. Parents say, you know
how hard

43:55.933 --> 44:00.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I worked to make money for you?
