44:26.163 --> 44:27.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of success in life.

44:27.431 --> 44:31.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Like getting a
degree or starting
a career.

44:31.068 --> 44:35.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kobliner also touts a trendy
gimmick for teaching
kids the uses of money.

44:35.773 --> 44:38.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: There are three
different jars
here. One is for...

44:38.976 --> 44:39.944 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILDREN: Savings.

44:39.977 --> 44:41.712 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: This one is for?

44:41.746 --> 44:42.713 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILDREN: Spending.

44:42.747 --> 44:44.815 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: And this one is
for?

44:44.849 --> 44:46.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILDREN: Sharing.

44:46.851 --> 44:52.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: The key concept
here, opportunity
cost. If you spend, you don't
have the opportunity

44:52.423 --> 44:53.791 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to save or share.

44:53.824 --> 44:56.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: Which do you want
to do? Do
you want to save it?

44:56.394 --> 44:57.995 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
CHILD: Share it.

44:58.029 --> 45:01.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: You want to share
it? What
would you do? You can either
save it...

45:01.966 --> 45:04.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHILD: Oh, my gosh. I know which
one.

45:04.402 --> 45:06.137 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: Which one? Tell
me.

45:06.170 --> 45:07.605 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHILD: I'm under the table.

45:07.638 --> 45:08.606 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BETH KOBLINER: Spend.

45:08.639 --> 45:10.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Where are you,
Vera?

45:10.241 --> 45:12.076 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHILD: I'm under the table.

45:12.109 --> 45:15.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Those of you who
ducked out of
econ lectures in school might
sympathize with

45:15.613 --> 45:17.548 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Vera's time-out moment.

45:17.582 --> 45:19.116 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the professor, unfazed,
pushed on.

45:19.150 --> 45:23.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: So, why do you
want to spend
it? What would you spend it on?

45:23.588 --> 45:24.855 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CHILD: Minecraft toys.

45:24.889 --> 45:27.024 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: Minecraft toys.
Oh.

45:27.058 --> 45:31.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Whitleigh Wilks
