lower body mass
indexes.

46:55.179 --> 46:56.981 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Right.

46:57.014 --> 46:59.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: It feels at first
like, oh,
it's because these kids have
this strong moral

46:59.383 --> 47:00.351 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fiber.

47:00.384 --> 47:01.419 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And higher I.Q. or
something.

47:01.452 --> 47:03.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BETH KOBLINER: And they're able
to resist
it.

47:03.454 --> 47:09.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we also know now it's more
the ability
to distract themselves. That's
an important

47:09.794 --> 47:16.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
